y underestimated with large systematic\nuncertainties, which can be related to the contribution of pairing effect and\nangular momentum. The recently observed superallowed decay from $^{104}$Te to\n$^{100}$Sn is also discussed based on uncertainty analysis. (Abstract is not\nfully presented because of length limitation)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Apr 2020 12:52:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
